Introduction¶

Selected dataset: noshowappointments¶

Description: This dataset collects information from 100k medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment. A number of characteristics about the patient are included in each row.

The Questions posed:

  • What is the overall percentage of showing up on the appointment day with a relation to who didnt?
  • Is the Gender associated with patient decision?
  • Does the location of the hospital affect the patient decision of coming to it on the scheduled date?
  • Does the age of the patient have any correlation to their decision?
  • Does a certain feature (Scholarship , SMS-received) have an influence on the patient decision?
  • How is the patient decision does gets affected by their current health status? (any type of illness)

Definitions of Some Repetitive Functions¶

In [28]:
#
#hue="Children" palette="plasma"
def Sns_Barcharts(Frame, Label,title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(7,7))
    ax = sns.countplot(x=Label, data=Frame)
    plt.xticks(rotation=-45)
    plt.title(title)
    #To show up the values of each bar.
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate(f'\n{p.get_height()}', (p.get_x()+0.2, p.get_height()), color='black', size=15)
    plt.show()
    return
In [29]:
#
def Sns_BarchartsGroupby(Frame,G1,G2,title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(7,7))
    ax = sns.countplot(x=G2, data=Frame[G1])
    plt.xticks(rotation=-45)
    plt.title(title)
    #To show up the values of each bar.
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate(f'\n{p.get_height()}', (p.get_x()+0.2, p.get_height()), color='black', size=15)
    plt.show()
    return
In [30]:
#
def Piecharts(Frame,Label,title):
    pie, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=[7,7])
    labels = Frame[Label].unique()
    plt.pie(x=Frame[Label].value_counts(), autopct="%1.2f%%", labels=labels, pctdistance=0.5)
    plt.title(title , fontsize=16)
    plt.show()
    return
In [31]:
#
def PiechartsGrouby(Frame, G1 , G2 ,title ):
    pie, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=[7,7])
    labels = Frame[G1].unique()
    plt.pie(x=Frame[G1][G2].value_counts(), autopct="%1.2f%%", labels=labels, pctdistance=0.5)
    plt.title(title , fontsize=16)
    plt.show()
    return

Conclusions¶

Major Findings :¶

So in conclusion we have answered all 6 questions we have posed aswell as done the analysis for all the features related to the patients ShowUp rates thus we conclude the following:

  • That the Over all ShowUp rate is >> 79.81% and the No show rate is >> 20.19%

  • That the Females Patients numbers are higher than Male Patients with a percentage of 65% to 35%, also that the gender doesnt really affect the attendance levels of the patients.

  • That on the Neighbourhood section we took top 10 ones visited by patients and we observed that JARDIM CAMBURI is the highest visited Neighbourhood with a percentage of appointment of 19.02% and a show up rate of 19.29%,So that can show us the affect of Neighbourhood on the patients attendance levels.

  • That the age group of which has the highest show up rates is Group D with 84.62% From 70 to 92 ,Also the lowest rates are Group A with 77.51% which is from 0 to 23,yet the most populated Group of the entire dataset is Group A with 31.37% of total population,Soby that we can see that Age does play a factor in ShowUp rates of the patients.

  • That the Percentage of patients who have a Scholarship Privilege are 9.83% and the their corresponding Show Up rates are 76.26% , Yet compared to the ratio of patients who doesnt have a Scholarship is somewhat higher with a percentage of 80.20% its clear that the Scholarship Privilege doesnt have any effect to the Patients Show up Rate.

  • That the ratio of the patients who did receive a sms as reminder is 32.10 of the whole population of the dataset,Thus the ShowUp percentage of them is 72.43% meanwhile compared to the patients who didnt receive a sms with a percentage of 83.30%, So it clear from this analysis that the SMS sent as a remainder doesnt have any effect Patients Show Rate.

  • That the total percentage of patients who have a Hypertension Problem are 19.73% & their corresponding Show up rates are 82.70% ,Yet the Show up rate of people who dont is 79.10% ,therefore the Hypertension of a patient does have an effect on the patients showup rates.

  • That the total percentage of patients who have a Diabetes Problem are 7.19% & their corresponding Show up rates are 82.00% ,Yet the Show up rate of people who dont is 79.64% ,therefore the Diabetes does have a slight effect on the patients showup rates.

  • That the total percentage of patients who Are Alcoholic are 3.04% & their corresponding Show up rates are 79.85% ,Yet the Show up rate of people who are not is 79.81% ,Hence we can say that Alcoholism doesnt really have any effect on the attendance rates of the patients.

  • That the total percentage of patients who have any level of handicap is 3% & their corresponding Show up rates are as follows : 82.16% for level 1 did show up in their appointment day while 17.87% didnt. Level 2 have a show up rate of 79.78% & 20.22% No show rates Level 3 have a show up rate of 76.92% & 23.08% No show rates Level 4 have a show up rate of 66.67% & 33.33% No show rates, Hence according to this analysis we can say that the handicap level of a patient does have an effect on their attendance rates.

Limitations¶

  • We could do a more deep analysis & inspection for the inner-relation & co-relation of different features togther such as Gender with Sms Sent , Alcoholism , Diabetes etc .. that might have any more indications for what does have a high impact on Attendance levels of the patients.

  • Dataset does lack some important information about location of each patient since its might have a correlation with patients Show up rates.

  • Further analysis & inspection could be done with the ScheduledDay ,AppointmentDay to get the ammount of time each patient wait till they need to show up.

  • The visualization of analysis and the data set information is restricted due to project scope.
